owl:Ontology.terms:description: An ontology to describe cohorts of patients participating in ENIGMA projects.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: The PD Demographics Ontology

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A homepage for some thing.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: homepage

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the brain scan data types that were collected for a cohort or project
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has brain scan data type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that indicates the cohort groups part of a cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has cohort group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the subcohorts, specific to a given project, that are part of that cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has cohort project

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that points to the person that is a contact for the project or cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has contact

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the control group of a cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has control group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the data types that a cohort or project collected
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has data type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that links a cohort project with the data being described.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has dataset

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the patient group of a cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has diagnostic group

owl:ObjectProperty.vann:example: Cohort1 hasDiagnosticInstrument miniInternationalNeuropychiatricInterview --> The members of Cohort1 are diagnosed with Mini International Neuropychiatric Interview
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes what instrument is used to diagnose the members of the cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has diagnostic instrument

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a downloadable form of a dataset at a specific location
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has distribution

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the genetic data types that were collected for a cohort or project
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has genetic data type

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the acquisition protocol that was used to scan the data of a cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has image acquisition protocol

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describe the investigators of a cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has person role investigator

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes which cohorts somone is a main PI of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has main person role principal investigator

owl:ObjectProperty.vann:example: Cohort1 hasPrincipalInvestigator John --> the principal investigator of Cohort1 is John
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the principal investigator of the cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has person role principal investigator

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the population group of a population-based cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has population group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property to link project results to a Cohort Project
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has project results

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property used to link a cohort with the summary statistics that may have been produced after applying a given protocol
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has statistics

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes demographics properties specific to the PD working group
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has PD demographics

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that indicates the cohort groups and cohort projects which are part of a cohort
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of cohort

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that indicates the cohort groups which are part of a cohort project

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that indicates the cohort groups specific to a project
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of project

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that indicates the cohorts which are a part of a working group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that indicates which project/working group studies which disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Dataset

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A mental health disorder defined by feelings of anxiety, fear, or worry
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Anxiety Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies the kinds of brain scan data collected
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Brain Scan Data Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A disease characterized by abnormal cell division and growth

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A subset of vascular disorders affecting the heart

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A subset of vascular disorders affecting blood vessels of the brain and cerebral circulation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Cognitive Covariates measured by each PD cohort

owl:Class.vann:example: AMCControlGroup is a control cohort group of the AMC cohort
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A subset of Cohort, which either forms the patient group or control group

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The subset of the individuals from a Cohort, which are used as samples for a specific project
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cohort Project

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Country in which a cohort is located

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Dataset in downloadable form

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies the kinds of data collected
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A dataset containing information about an ENIGMA project cohort
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dataset

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The method used to diagnose individuals in a Cohort
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Diagnostic Instrument

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A disorder/disease experienced by members of a cohort
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Disorders which affect the endocrine system
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Endocrine Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies the kinds of genetic data collected
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Genetic Data Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Disorders which are inherited and caused by abnormalities in the genome
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Genetic Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Procedure used to collect image data within the cohort
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image Acquisition Protocol

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A disease or disorder caused by the invasion of microorganisms

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Geographic location of the cohort

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Disorders which can affect mood, behavior, and thinking

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mood Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Disorders which affect the nervous system

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Project associated with the cohort
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Project

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Disorders which affect the respiratory system
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Respiratory Disorder

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Blanket term ecompassing serious medical condtions

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A mental health disorder defined by the overusage or abuse of a substance
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Substance Abuse

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A subset of substance abuse in which symptoms of withdrawal may appeared after reduction of substance use
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Substance Dependence

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Disorder which affects the body's network of blood vessels
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Vascular Disorder
